# Backwards Incompatible Changes

I've made some updates to the environment variable listed below.

## Removed `TRACKER_EXECUTION_ORDER` CLOUDFLARE-CHECK value

All cloudflare verifications are handled like other manual user inputs, so we only have two types: **HEADLESS** and **MANUAL**.

## New default for `REDACTION_TYPE`

Now that I'm comfortable with the overlay redaction, I am changing the default type from **TEXT** to **BOX** (new options described below). This will only impact users that didn't explicitly set the `REDACTION_TYPE` option in their `docker run` command.

## Renamed `REDACTION_TYPE` OVERLAY value

I have removed the **OVERLAY** value from `REDACTION_TYPE` and renamed it **BOX**. The functionality has not changed, just the name.

# Other changes

## New `REDACTION_TYPE` value

Added the value **BLUR** which will add a Gaussian blur effect over sensitive information, instead of the solid block with title performed by the **BOX** option. See screenshots for an example.

## Improved overlay redaction

I've gone through every tracker to ensure overlay redaction is consistently covering sensitive information.

## Profile page confirmation

Each tracker now confirms that the user profile page has loaded prior to taking screenshots/redacting elements, so any failures should be clearer.

## New/updated trackers

Added or updated the UI for 20 or so trackers. See README.md for the full list of supported trackers.

## Retaining prefixes during redaction

When redacting a torrent or IRC passkey, the prefix (`Passkey:` or `IRC Key:`) is now kept unredacted.

## Removal of Python

I was using some Python code to assist with bypassing Cloudflare detection through Java, but now I patch the binary in the Docker image so no Python is needed at runtime.
